The paper deals with the study of automatic presentations of algebraic structures, which involves topics such as regular languages, automata theory, and logic. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic (cs.LO) or Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the isomorphism problem for automatic structures, which is a topic in computational complexity theory, indicating that the paper could also be classified under the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category. The paper also mentions the free Abelian group and Fraisse limits, which are topics in algebra and model theory, respectively, suggesting that the paper could be classified under the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories.
